cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.CG, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing peer-to-peer networks and their underlying data. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel geometric method for characterizing different types of networks. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing network structures. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper adapts the classical Ricci flow to undirected and weighted networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with change detection in large dynamic data sets.
